SimulateAssetType.description:
Asset type returned when calling {@link TransactNamespace.simulateAssetChanges }.
Allows you to determine if the assets approved or / and transferred are
native, tokens or NFTs.

SimulateChangeType.description: Change type returned when calling {@link TransactNamespace.simulateAssetChanges }.

SimulateAssetChangesChange.description:
Represents an asset change from a call to
{@link TransactNamespace.simulateAssetChanges }.

assetType.description: The type of asset from the transaction.

changeType.description: The type of change from the transaction.

rawAmount.description:
The raw amount as an integer string. Only available on TRANSFER changes for
NATIVE and ERC20 assets, or ERC721/ERC1155 disapprove changes (field set to
'0').

amount.description:
The amount as an integer string. This value is calculated by applying the
`decimals` field to the `rawAmount` field. Only available on TRANSFER
changes for NATIVE and ERC20 assets, or ERC721/ERC1155 disapprove changes
(field set to '0').

name.description: The name of the asset transferred, if available.

symbol.description: The symbol of the asset transferred if available.

decimals.description:
The number of decimals used by the ERC20 token. Set to 0 for APPROVE
changes. Field is undefined if it's not defined in the contract and not
available from other sources.

contractAddress.description:
The contract address of the asset. Only applicable to ERC20, ERC721,
ERC1155, NFT and SPECIAL_NFT transactions.

logo.description: URL for the logo of the asset, if available. Only applicable to ERC20 transactions.

tokenId.description:
The token id of the asset transferred. Only applicable to ERC721,
ERC1155 and SPECIAL_NFT NFTs.

SimulateAssetChangesError.description:
The error field returned in a {@link SimulateAssetChangesResponse} if the
simulation failed.

SimulateAssetChangesResponse.description: Response object for the {@link TransactNamespace.simulateAssetChanges } method.

changes.description: An array of asset changes that resulted from the transaction.

gasUsed.description:
The amount of gas used by the transaction represented as a hex string. The
field is undefined if an error occurred.

error.description: Optional error field that is present if an error occurred.

tokenId.description: The asset's token ID, or null if ERC-20

tokenStandard.description: The token standard (e.g. "ERC721") for this asset
